BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:narrative-logging-check-20260324@predictor-ingest
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T113000
SUMMARY:Check narrative logging output after fix
DESCRIPTION:After today's film pipeline run\, review the trending stage stdout for the new narrative instrumentation lines:\n\n  - N LLM narratives returned\n  - N narratives mapped to entity IDs\n  - N name mismatches dropped\n  - N narrative context skipped\n\nExpected: narrativesLlmReturned ~10\, narrativesMapped close to that\, mismatches near 0.\nIf mismatches are high\, the LLM is using different names than the DB — consider normalizing entity names in context or prompting with entity_id alongside name.\nIf LlmReturned < top_n\, model is under-generating — check prompt or raise top_n.
CATEGORIES:Backend,Task
STATUS:NEEDS-ACTION
PRIORITY:3
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT10M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Check narrative logging output
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:badge-contrast-fix-20260324@predictor-ingest
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T150000
SUMMARY:Fix badge gray-on-gray contrast issues
DESCRIPTION:Badge contrast regression — gray-on-gray still appearing in some situations.\nInvestigate which badge variants are affected.\nDefault .badge: white text on --gray-500 background.\nCheck dark mode token values and entity types falling through to default styling.\nPrevious fix: film domain badge contrast fixes (10 new type rules)\, default badge white-on-gray for dark mode.\n\nReference: branch fix/hot-panel-bounce-and-narrative has the intended changes but conflicts with main — cherry-pick the badge.css\, button.css\, toolbar.css diffs manually rather than merging.
CATEGORIES:UI,Task
STATUS:NEEDS-ACTION
PRIORITY:3
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT10M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Badge contrast fix scheduled
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
